
=========================================
Make .tar
=========================================

making a .tar from learn linux TV

copy entire etc/ folder to current dir

$ sudo cp -r /etc . 

	- copy recursively /dir current foler

check to see its in their 

$ ls

then set ownership to full you 

	stay in the parent dir

$ sudo chown bobbie:bobbie -R etc 

	- change ownership bobbie: recursively for etc 
		note dont use / at the end of etc

create .tar 

$ tar -cf etc_backup.tar etc

check contents 

$ tar -tf etc_backup.tar 

you could even pipe the word count and line count as well

$ tar -tf etc_backup.tar | wc -l



